<!--
    FOOD PAGE

    Used to dynamically load the food page
    To convince people to donate if they cant volunteer.
    
-->
<link href="/css/food.css" rel="stylesheet">
<body>
    <div class="content">
        <div class="donate-page-container">
            <h1>Support Pu Ngaol</h1>
            <p>If you are unable to physically volunteer in Pu Ngaol, you can still make a significant impact by donating. Your contributions will help us provide essential resources and infrastructure to improve the lives of the villagers.</p>
            <div class="donate-section">
                <h2>Why Donate?</h2>
                <p>Your donations will directly support projects such as building wells, constructing houses, and providing educational materials. Every contribution, no matter the size, makes a difference.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Direct Impact:</strong> Your funds will be used to directly benefit the community.</li>
                    <li><strong>Transparency:</strong> We provide regular updates on how donations are being utilized.</li>
                    <li><strong>Community Development:</strong> Your support helps build a sustainable future for Pu Ngaol.</li>
                </ul>
                <button class="donate-button" onclick="showDonationForm()">Donate Now</button>
                <div id="donation-form" class="hidden">
                    <h3>Enter Donation Amount</h3>
                    <form>
                        <label for="amount">Amount (Â£):</label>
                        <input type="number" id="amount" name="amount" min="1" required>
                        <button type="submit">Submit Donation</button>
                    </form>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script>
        function showDonationForm() {
            document.getElementById('donation-form').classList.toggle('hidden');
        }
    </script>
</body>